Communicated by:
Mahmoud Orabi
<ahstandards@gmail.com>

[ProMED thanks Mahmoud Orabi for sending this important update on measles in the DRC.

Kasongo, also known as Piani Kasongo, is a town and territory in Maniema province of the eastern Democratic Republic of the Congo.

DR Congo is burdened with Ebola in the eastern region of the country, COVID, low vaccination rates to measles, underfunding of its healthcare system, political violence, and more. According to Doctors Without Borders/Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF), between 2018 and 2020, more than 460 000 children contracted measles, and nearly 8000 died from it, 3/4 of which were under 5 years old. Increased manpower and funding are needed to vaccinate the children to protect them against this highly infectious disease. - Mod.LK]

******
[2] Outbreak summary DRC
Date: Tue 19 Oct 2021
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/measles-in-the-drc-more-than-40k-cases-reported-year-to-date-99923/


From the beginning of the year [1 Jan 2021] through the end of September 2021, the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC) reported 41 099 suspected measles cases and 991 confirmed, including 603 deaths (CFR 1.5%) in 369 health districts across 26 provinces of the country.

The outbreak has been confirmed in 82 health districts across 23 affected provinces including the capital city of Kinshasa.

In August 2020, the DRC declared the end of a 25-month outbreak of measles that claimed the lives of more than 7000 children aged under 5.

However, earlier this year [2021], Doctors Without Borders/Medecins Sans Frontieres (MSF) reported the rise in measles once again.

In addition to measles, DRC reports outbreaks of cholera, meningitis, monkeypox, plague, typhoid fever, COVID-19, and the 13th Ebola virus disease outbreak in the country's history.

